<br>
Level 58 bard gains:<br>
Riposte Skill - improved defensive ability.<br>
Jonthan's Inspiration - self only<br>
Niv's Harmonic - group AC buff (with amp +62 AC)<br>
Chorus of Replenishment - AOE mana song<br>
<br>
Let me babble about AoE mana song for a couple...<br>
<br>
<br>
THE GOOD:<br>
This is a very strong song that will help us raid better. With epic it is 12 mana regen per tick (C3 = 14 mana per tick, C2 = 11 mana per tick), and is 21 hitpoints regen per tick (regrowth of the grove = 15 hitpoints per tick). Don't worry it still stacks with Clarity spells and regeneration spells too...<br>
<br>
It is AoE so it works if you are in range of the song. It does not have a large range. It is your responsibility to be in range of the song if you want the buff. I will try to stand still - sometimes.<br>
<br>
This song is exactly like casting any buff or group buff. It does not pull things of its own accord. If it is &quot;safe&quot; for the cleric to buff, then it is &quot;safe&quot; for me to sing aoe mana.<br>
<br>
<br>
THE BAD:<br>
I will be singing this song when I feel it is appropriate. Please do not ask me to sing it, unless you see me being a dunce with the wrong song on during an extended down period. If I reply &quot;no&quot; ... please accept that I have a good reason not to sing it at the moment.<br>
<br>
This song is very dangerous to the bard. Lets say I pulse this during a fight on a 4 group raid... the song lasts 3 ticks and heals 21 per tick on 24 characters: bard boy gets credit for healing 1512 points of damage plus the mana regen. There are times where that may = dead bard. The worst time is while a creature is being pulled.<br>
<br>
<br>
THE UGLY:<br>
I would love to leave this song on in towns... but I will not. Lets say someone that is KoS runs through town. They zone after I cast my aoe healing buff on them. Result is I'm standing around in town minding my own business and humming my magical tune, and suddenly every guard in the zone starts beating on me... &quot;/gu rez please.&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Also a character that has agro, that heals another character does cause agro on the character healed. So AoE mana can be used to train others - something I shall need to careful with.<br>
<br>
